About Worldcoin (WLD)

World, formerly known as Worldcoin, is a partially decentralized, community governed, blockchain project that was launched in July 2023 by OpenAIs Sam Altman, alongside Alex Blania and Max Novendstern. Worldcoin was founded in order to prove human identity online, to differentiate real users from bots or AI agents.
Its native cryptocurrency is called WLD. It is an ERC-20 token that is compatible with the Ethereum network. You can receive WLD tokens by providing your biometric data. To do so, your iris is scanned using a device called the Orb. This process creates a unique World ID. Biometric data of your retina is then converted into a cryptographic hash in order to maintain user privacy. According to World, biometric data is not stored onchain, meaning in theory it is not accessible to hackers.
WLD launched in July 24, 2023.
Today, WLDs main use case is for digital verification, governance, and reward campaigns. WLD holders are often from emerging markets or countries where access to stable financial and digital systems is limited.

  • How do I bridge Worldcoin?

    Bridging crypto across chains allows you to move tokens from one network to another. With MetaMask, bridging Worldcoin (WLD) is easy, secure, and cost-effective. Our aggregator finds the most efficient routes to move your digital assets from one chain to another. And with cross-chain swapping, bridging and swapping can take place at the same time in a single transaction. Meaning: instead of bridging WLD from chain A and wrapping or unwrapping it on chain B, you can swap WLD from chain A to a second token on chain B, all in one move.

  • What can you do with Worldcoin?

    With Worldcoin, you can send and receive WLD, the networks native token, and use it to pay transaction fees on certain networks. WLD is supported in decentralized apps for trading, staking, yield optimization, and payments. You can participate in DeFi protocols, bridge assets between networks, or use WLD in select web3 financial strategies, all with Ethereum-compatible speed and flexibility.

  • How do I trade Worldcoin for other cryptocurrencies?

    Trading Worldcoin (WLD) for ETH, WBTC, or SOL can be done directly in MetaMask. For more information on how to swap WLD, head to MetaMask Support.
